title: sklearn.ensemble.RandomForestRegressor builds incorrect shap_values object and selection fails
body:
The following code in SHAP 0.38.1 and RandomForestRegressor (v0.23.2) fails, while in SHAP 0.37 run ok.
If I use XGBRegressor (v1.3.3)  it woks ok, too.

Code:
```python
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestRegressor
from xgboost import XGBRegressor
import shap

model = RandomForestRegressor(random_state=123)
#model =XGBRegressor(objective='reg:squarederror')
model.fit(X,y)

explainer_new = shap.Explainer(model)
shap_values_new = explainer_new(X)

print(shap_values_new[:,0])
```
Output:
```
TypeError                                 Traceback (most recent call last)
<ipython-input-68-093e207dddf4> in <module>()
----> 1 shap_values_new[:,0]

/usr/local/lib/python3.6/dist-packages/sklearn/ensemble/_base.py in __getitem__(self, index)
    167     def __getitem__(self, index):
    168         """Return the index'th estimator in the ensemble."""
--> 169         return self.estimators_[index]
    170 
    171     def __iter__(self):
```
TypeError: list indices must be integers or slices, not tuple
